SUMMARY:Dumpling Diplomacy Holds Fundraiser for IMANI
DESCRIPTION:One box of dumplings is an investment in a student’s future. That’s the idea behind this year’s First Annual Patricio Fundraiser sponsored by social enterprise Dumpling Diplomacy to benefit longtime Montclair nonprofit IMANI. \nThe two organizations are coming together on March 14 to raise money for programs aimed at closing the longstanding achievement/opportunity gap in Montclair. The afternoon event\, which will be held at The Mark\, is a chance for the community to purchase delicious dumplings\, mingle with their neighbors\, and support a good cause. \nFour different types of dumplings will be available for pre-order: IMANI Signature Spicy Jerk Chicken\, Chicken & Corn\, Fussy Vegan (vegetarian)\, and Ricotta\, Parmesan & Spinach. \nDumplings will only be available for pre-order\, but patrons can choose to pick them up or dine on site and strike up a conversation with new friends. Tables will be set up inside the church\, and refreshments will be available for purchase. \nThe fundraiser is underway and will culminate on Saturday\, March 14 from 3 p.m. to 5 p.m. at The Mark: St. Mark’s United Methodist Church\, 51 Elm Street\, Montclair. \nShare this:\n				Share on Facebook (Opens in new window)\n				Facebook\n			\n				Share on Bluesky (Opens in new window)\n				Bluesky\n			\n				Share on LinkedIn (Opens in new window)\n				LinkedIn\n			\n				Share on Threads (Opens in new window)\n				Threads\n			\n				Share on Nextdoor (Opens in new window)\n				Nextdoor\n			\n				Share on WhatsApp (Opens in new window)\n				WhatsApp\n			\n				Email a link to a friend (Opens in new window)\n				Email
URL:https://montclairlocal.news/event/dumpling-diplomacy-holds-fundraiser-for-imani/
